Mid-Term Project¶

Overview¶

  • Use Medicare CCLF Claims from Syntegra dataset to answer key business questions
  • Extra credit for building up on the questions below (additional questions + answers)
  • One Jupyter notebook solution with clear Python code and all cell outputs available
  • At least two data quality checks

Step 0. Prepare raw input datasets¶

Here we will 1) load original datasets, 2) remove unused columns, 3) de-duplicate rows, and 4) join datasets, not necessarily in this order

Assumptions:

  • Claim ID (cur_clm_uniq_id) represents one claim, which may or may not have more than one code (code could be HCPCS/CPT, diagnosis, procedure...)
  • There is a one-to-many relationship between patient IDs (bene_mbi_id) and claim IDs (cur_clm_uniq_id), i.e. each claim is unique to one patient, but one patient can have more than one claim

Business insights:

Over the previous few years, the proportion of CVM claims to all claims has been gradually rising, from 12.88% in 2016 to 13.87% in 2017 and 2018. This pattern implies that CVM illnesses have become more common and complicated, necessitating more medical treatments. It's also feasible that modifications to Medicare reimbursement guidelines or coding standards are to blame for the rising percentage of CVM claims.

Pharmaceutical businesses have both opportunities and challenges as a result of this shift. Pharmaceutical businesses that specialize in CVM disorders are well-positioned to capitalize on the growing market for CVM treatments. Conversely, pharmaceutical companies must devise approaches to tackle the difficulties associated with managing CVM disorders, including but not limited to creating more economical and efficient therapies and enhancing patient compliance with prescribed regimens.

Pharmaceutical companies could perform additional analyses, such as analyzing the share of CVM claims by type of procedure, patient demographics, and geographic region, to gain a better understanding of the trends in CVM claims and to create more focused and efficient sales and marketing strategies for CVM products.

def assign_segment(age):
    if 18 <= age <= 59:
        return 'Patients with age 18-59'
    elif 60 <= age <= 69:
        return 'Patients with age 60-69'
    elif 70 <= age <= 79:
        return 'Patients with age 70-79'
    elif age >= 80:
        return 'Patients with age 80+'
    else:
        return 'Other'

# Applying the function to create the 'Segment' column
cardiac_df['Segment'] = cardiac_df['patient_age'].apply(assign_segment)

    percentage_change_17_18 = ((pivot_table_selected.loc[2018] - pivot_table_selected.loc[2017]) / pivot_table_selected.loc[2017]) * 100

Business insights:

Patients between the ages of 18 and 59 had the highest number of CVM claims. More than 70% of CVM claims fall into this age range.Patients between the ages of 60 and 69 are seeing a higher rate of growth in CVM claims than patients in other age groups. This implies that the usage of CVM treatments and products is increasing within this age group.There are fewer CVM claims for patients who are 80 years of age or older. This could be because complex medical issues requiring more specialist treatment are more common in older persons.

Marketing implications:

Pharmaceutical businesses ought to concentrate their marketing efforts on patients between the ages of 60 and 69 and 18 to 59. These are the age categories where CVM claims are most prevalent and where they are growing the fastest.Pharmaceutical firms want to create advertising strategies that are customized to each age group's unique requirements and preferences. Campaigns aimed at patients between the ages of 18 and 59, for instance, would emphasize the advantages of early diagnosis and treatment, whereas those aimed at patients between the ages of 60 and 69 might concentrate on managing chronic illnesses and enhancing quality of life.To target a range of age groups, pharmaceutical businesses should employ a number of marketing methods. This could involve both digital and traditional media, like social media and search engine optimization, as well as advertising in print and television.

Example of a marketing campaign:

A pharmaceutical business might create a marketing campaign aimed at patients between the ages of 60 and 69. The advantages of employing CVM goods and therapies to treat long-term illnesses including diabetes, arthritis, and heart disease could be the campaign's main message. Numerous media platforms, including social media, direct mail, and print and television advertising, might be used to distribute the campaign.

The following messaging could be part of the campaign:

"CVM products can help you manage your chronic condition and improve your quality of life." "Talk to your doctor about whether CVM products are right for you." "Visit our website to learn more about CVM products and treatments."

Patient testimonies from those who have effectively managed their chronic diseases with CVM products could potentially be used in the marketing.

A pharmaceutical business might create a marketing campaign similar to this one to target older persons who use CVM treatments and products.
